accessibility.info:
Accessible seating is available on the main floor only.

MAIN FLOOR: section three rows WC1, WC2 & WC3, and sections two and three in row KK.

Hearing Impaired should purchase best available seats on the regular purchase page.  Listening devices are available to aid hearing impaired persons.  A patron needs to bring a drivers license or credit card to an usher to obtain a device.  The signal is sent through the house directly from the sound board.

If you require ASL interpretation, Audio Description or Open Captioning, please contact the box office at 612-339-7007 or at accessible@broadwayacrossamerica.com to inquire about availability of those services for your desired event.

venues.name: State Theatre

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Sun: Closed Mon-Fri: 10:00am - 5:00pm Sat: 12 noon - 3:00pm
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, Visa, Mastercard, American Express, and Discover are accepted.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will Call can be picked up no earlier than 90 minutes prior to the performance at the State Theate Box Office. Customers must present a picture ID, the credit card used for purchase and the order number.

venues.parkingDetail: There is ample parking in the area. There are flat lots on the corner of 10th St and Hennepin Avenue. There are also ramps located at Marshall Fields, LaSalle Plaza, Target Center, or municipal ramps. The State Theatre recommends using the Hawthorne ramp at 9th Street & First Avenue. The State Theatre is also accessible by the downtown skyway system.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Wheelchair accessible seating is available on the main floor only, as there is no elevator to the balcony. Seating is in Section 3, Rows K and L, and Section 1, Row KK. Hearing devices are available. Please bring a drivers liscense or credit card to an usher to obtain a device.

generalInfo.generalRule: The State Theatre is a gun-free facility. We prohibit weapons in or on our Theatre grounds. Cameras and recording devices are not allowed. Pagers and cell phones must be checked with an usher or the box office.
generalInfo.childRule: Everyone must have a ticket. Children under 6 years of age are discouraged from attending unless the performance is intended for young audiences. Anyone being distruptive will be asked to leave, and no refund will be given. Babysitters may call 612-339-7007 to contact parents. Please be sure the sitter has the seat location of your tickets, since the theatre is not equiped with a paging system. The exact seat location is comprised of a section number, row letter and seat number.

events.name: U.S. Bank Stadium Tour
events.info: Your ninety-minute guided adventure through U.S. Bank Stadium will give you behind-the-scenes access to the new home of the Minnesota Vikings. Discover the inner workings of U.S. Bank Stadium including VIP-accessible only clubs and suites, the press box, the art collection, team locker room, stadium floor, and so much more. Our Tour Guides are knowledgeable and are well-versed on building architecture, Vikings history, and sustainability features of U.S. Bank Stadium. All public and private tours are wheelchair accessible, and complimentary wheelchairs are available upon request (subject to availability). Specific tour routes are established each day based on events and activities in the stadium, therefore all sites on the tour are subject to current availability.
events.pleaseNote: All tours begin at the Box Office located at the Polaris Gate near Chicago and 4th Street and are approximately 90 minutes long. Make sure to wear comfortable shoes as tours cover a distance of approximately one mile. Tours are will run every hour starting at 10:00 AM with the last tour departing at 4:00 PM every day except Sundays. On Sundays, tours will run every hour starting at 11:00 AM with the last tour departing at 3:00 PM. Tours will not be offered on Vikings game days and other blackout dates. Group tours must be booked at least two weeks in advance. Discounted tickets will require proof of ID. Please have your military/student ID with you on your tour.

accessibility.info: All public and private tours are wheelchair accessible, and complimentary wheelchairs are available upon request (subject to availability). For any guest requiring special assistance please call 612 777-8776.

venues.name: Pantages Theatre

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: The Pantages box office is only open on days that there is a performance at the Theatre. On show days the box office open at 5:00 pm, or two hours before the first show if there is a matinee. Tickets may be purchased in advance at the State Theatre box office at 805 Hennepin Avenue (one block south across the street). The hours at the State Theatre are: Mon-Fri: 10:00am - 6:00pm Sat: 12:noon - 3:00pm Sun: Closed
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, Visa, MasterCard, American Express and Discover are accepted.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will call is available for pickup beginning an hour and a half prior to showtime at the Box Office in the main lobby. Tickets will only be released if you have a valid photo ID and the Ticketmaster order number.

venues.parkingDetail: There is ample parking in the area. Flat lots are located on the corner of 10th Street and Hennepin Avenue. Ramps are located at Marshall Fields, LaSalle Plaza, The Conservatory, Target Center, or municipal ramps. The Pantages Theatre suggests parking at the Hawthorne Ramp behind the Orpheum Theatre. All are within easy walking distance of the Theatre.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Accessible seating is located on the main floor and balcony. An elevator is available to the balcony. An interpreter can be arranged per your request. Listening devices are available to aid hearing impaired persons. You will need to bring a drivers license or credit card to an usher to obtain a device. The signal is sent through the house directly from the sound board.

generalInfo.generalRule: The Pantages Theatre is a gun-free facility. We prohibit weapons in or on our Theatre grounds. No cameras, recording devices, or outside food or beverage allowed.
generalInfo.childRule: Children ages six and under will not be admitted to any show unless otherwise noted. Every patron needs a ticket, regardless of age. Anyone being disruptive will be asked to leave, and no refund will be given. Please give the babysitter your seat number, row letter, section number, and the emergency phone number 612-339-7007 so that you may be located in the event of an emergency. The Theatre has no paging system, so they must be able to locate you by the exact seating location.
